cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with the problem of representing the semantics of words, which is a core problem in natural language processing, making cs.CL the most likely category.
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper proposes to integrate visual context to learn multimodal word embeddings, which involves the use of computer vision techniques, making cs.CV a likely category.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes an end-to-end method to integrate visual context elements in a multimodal skip-gram model, which involves the use of machine learning techniques, making cs.LG a likely category.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with the problem of representing the semantics of words, which is a core problem in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI a likely category.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the integration of textual and visual context to learn multimodal word embeddings, which involves the use of multimedia techniques, making cs.MM a possible category.
